            "title": "Japan Retail Sales Growth Above Forecasts",
            "description": "<div class=\"body-KX2tCBZq body-pIO_GYwT content-pIO_GYwT\"><div class=\"symbolsContainer-cBh_FN2P logosContainer-cwMMKgmm\" data-no-swipe=\"true\"></div><div><span><p class=\"\"><span>Retail sales in Japan climbed 1.0% year-on-year in November 2025, slowing from a 1.7% growth in the previous month but surpassing market expectations for a 0.8% increase.</span></p><p class=\"\"><span>It marked the third consecutive month of growth, supported by sales in machinery and equipment (7.1%), pharmaceuticals and cosmetics (5.6%), automobiles (3.9%), other retail categories (3.8%),  department stores (2.0%), and food and beverages (1.1%).</span></p></span></div></div>",
